    "answer_id" : 2650192,
    "question_id" : 2650168,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p><strong>Compiling</strong> is the act of turning source code into object code.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Linking</strong> is the act of combining object code with libraries into a raw executable.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Building</strong> is the sequence composed of <strong>compiling</strong> and <strong>linking</strong>, with possibly other tasks such as installer creation.</p>\n\n<p>Many compilers handle the <strong>linking</strong> step automatically after compiling source code.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/2310261/what-is-the-difference-between-compiling-and-building\">What is the difference between compile code and executable code?</a></p>\n"
  }, {
